              <tr><td>Spinal decompression</td><td>Passive hang</td><td>Maximum vertebral separation</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Shoulder rehab</td><td>Passive hang, neutral grip</td><td>Joint-friendly with full capsular stretch</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Pull-up prep</td><td>Active hang</td><td>Scapular depression strength</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Core training</td><td>L-hang, mixed grip</td><td>Anti-rotation and hip flexor demand</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Climbing</td><td>Towel, one-arm</td><td>Pinch grip and single-arm endurance</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>Most training programs combine 2-3 variations across a week. Alternate between grip types and shoulder positions for balanced development. The <a href="/training-programs/">structured training programs</a> integrate multiple variations into weekly schedules.</p>

